      <preamble>
         <p>The Scottish Ministers make the following Order in exercise of the power conferred by section 43(5) of the Title Conditions (Scotland) Act 2003<noteRef href="#f00001" class="footnote" marker="1"/> and all other powers enabling them to do so.</p>
         <formula name="enactingText">
            <p>They are satisfied as to the matters mentioned in section 43(6)<noteRef href="#f00002" class="footnote" marker="2"/> of that Act.</p>
         </formula>
      </preamble>
      <body>
         <article eId="article-1">
            <heading>Citation and commencement</heading>
            <num>1.</num>
            <content>
               <p>This Order may be cited as the Title Conditions (Scotland) Act 2003 (Rural Housing Bodies) Amendment Order 2019 and comes into force on 30 June 2019.</p>
            </content>
         </article>
         <article eId="article-2">
            <heading>Amendment of the list of prescribed rural housing bodies</heading>
            <num>2.</num>
            <paragraph eId="article-2-1">
               <num>(1)</num>
               <content>
                  <p>The schedule of the Title Conditions (Scotland) Act 2003 (Rural Housing Bodies) Order 2004<noteRef href="#f00003" class="footnote" marker="3"/> (rural housing bodies prescribed under section 43(5) of the Title Conditions (Scotland) Act 2003) is amended as follows.</p>
               </content>
            </paragraph>
            <paragraph eId="article-2-2">
               <num>(2)</num>
               <content>
                  <p>Before “Barra and Vatersay Housing Association Limited” insert—<mod>
                        <quotedStructure startQuote="“" endQuote="”" ukl:TargetClass="unknown" ukl:TargetSubClass="unknown" ukl:Context="unknown">
                           <p>Arran Development Trust</p>
                        </quotedStructure>
                     </mod>
                     <inline name="AppendText">.</inline>
                  </p>
               </content>
            </paragraph>
         </article>
